---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Repeaters"
  floatingImages={true}
  imageDir="hero-imgs/solar"
  imageCount={12}
>
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 pointer-events-auto">
    <article
      class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none
                  prose-headings:text-[var(--text-primary)]
                  prose-p:text-[var(--text-secondary)]
                  prose-a:text-blue-600 dark:prose-a:text-blue-400
                  prose-strong:text-[var(--text-primary)]
                  prose-code:text-[var(--text-primary)]
                  prose-code:bg-gray-100 dark:prose-code:bg-gray-800
                  prose-pre:bg-gray-100 dark:prose-pre:bg-gray-800
                  prose-blockquote:border-l-blue-500
                  prose-ul:text-[var(--text-secondary)]
                  prose-ol:text-[var(--text-secondary)]
                  prose-li:text-[var(--text-secondary)]
                  bg-[var(--bg-primary)] rounded-lg p-8 shadow-lg"
    >
      <h1>Repeaters</h1>

      <p>
        Most radios can be reflashed to become a repeater. The distinction is
        more the use case, and what we refer to here as a fixed repeater:
        something with batteries or solar panels for multi-day power,
        weather-proofed, and often fewer UI elements.
      </p>

      <h2>Some Devices</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://wiki.seeedstudio.com/meshtastic_solar_node/"
            >https://wiki.seeedstudio.com/meshtastic_solar_node/</a>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Radios and Repeater Devices to Consider</h3>

      <p>Spenser likes:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong
            ><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0F1MWPF7G/"
              >KEEPTEEN D5L Mesh Solar LoRa Repeater</a
            >:</strong
          > All in one. Sounds like it's well supported and well regarded. This is
          going to be my "plug and play" repeater for travel and events.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.amazon.com/RAKwireless-WisBlock-Meshtastic-Starter-RAK19007/dp/B0CHKZJK9C/"
              >WisBlock Meshtastic Starter Kit</a
            > & RAK Wireless Solar Unify Enclosure Case:</strong
          > This is going to be my experimental repeater for trying out code changes.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
